    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fd7a50ec_3e0adf2b",
        "filename": "common/proto/mask/mask.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 57,
      "author": {
        "id": 1381059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-18T23:50:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m also aware of this. A bit of context of why this imported is needed: \n\nIn this pkg, we need two functionalities\n\n1. Get protoreflect.Message[1] from v1 generated message\n2. Convert protoreflect.Message back to v1 message \n\nLuckily, there\u0027s a new version(1.4.0) of v1 library (still in release candidate) provides those functionalities out of box. We can implement the first by calling `proto.MessageReflect`[2] while the second by calling `proto.MessageV1`[3].\n\nI\u0027ve attempted update the version of consumed v1 library to 1.4.0. However, it turns out it requires some effort to accomplish this update as various tests are failing (TL;DR is test comparing library requires some tuning to compare the v2 generated proto)\n\nI looked into the implementation of aforementioned to function and realized protoimpl pkg encapsulates all the implementation details so I can call that pkg directly to achieve the same. Therefore, in order to quickly ship this feature first to unblock bb rewrite, I decide to go with this route first. Fixing all the tests and make sure we can upgrade to 1.4.0 is the next thing on my plate. After that, I will get rid of the import of protoimpl and switch to native function provided in v1 library.\n\nI will leave a todo here. Does that sounds good to you?\n\n\n[1]: https://pkg.go.dev/google.golang.org/protobuf@v1.20.1/reflect/protoreflect?tab\u003ddoc#Message\n[2]: https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/golang/protobuf@v1.4.0-rc.4/proto?tab\u003ddoc#MessageReflect\n[3]: https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/golang/protobuf@v1.4.0-rc.4/proto?tab\u003ddoc#MessageV1",
      "parentUuid": "3c61ed91_2ac9676d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 57,
        "startChar": 37,
        "endLine": 57,
        "endChar": 46
      },
